properties.areaDesc: Natrona County Lower Elevations; Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 1 at 2:12AM MST until February 2 at 3:00AM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High Wind Warning and Watches across portions of northern and
central Wyoming this morning through tonight...

.Strong winds aloft and a tight pressure gradient will combine
for high winds across the Cody Foothills and Absaroka Mountains
this morning into tonight. The strong winds will last across the
Absaroka Mountains through tonight. High winds across southeast
Fremont into Natrona County are likely today as well.

* WHAT...Southwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph.

* WHERE...Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range and Natrona County
Lower Elevations, especially along Outer Drive.

* WHEN...Until 3 AM MST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. A blow over risk for light
and high profile vehicles including camper trailers and semi
trucks.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM MST SUNDAY
